post_text:
Compton Unified School District schools will reopen schools on August 20, 2020 with distance learning only.

In accordance with #LACountyDepartmentofPublicHealth guidelines, the District has developed a detailed Reopening Protocols for Preschool - 12th (grade) Schools.

The plan includes: Workplace Policies and Practices; Measures to Ensure Physical Distancing; Measures to Ensure Infection Control; Communication Processes; Measures that Ensure Equitable Access To Critical Services and Protocol for COVID-19 Exposure Management. Please click the link to access the protocol.

http://www.compton.k12.ca.us/news-release/news/2020/august/reopen-protocols

Again, please note students will participate in learning virtually and not on school site campuses when the school year resumes.

July 8 at 7:52 PM Â·

Calling All High School Students!

Are you interested in the music industry? Are you a musician, or just want to learn more about the business of music itself?

IN JUST ONE WEEK, the Music Unites: Summer 2020 MusicVersity is launching a FREE, virtual summer program in partnership with the Compton Unified School District & Skullcandy.

Classes will be held once a week on Wednesdays - July 15th, July 22nd, July 29th and August 5th starting at 12:30pm PT/3:30pm ET.

Featuring executives from Rocnation, Columbia Records, LiveNation-Ticketmaster United Talent Agency,and artists such as Compton's Channel Tres, Grammy Award winning producer Linda Perry, Jon Batiste (The Late Show with Stephen Colbert), and artist/producer duo Social House (Ariana Grande/ Scooter Braun Projects).

Classes are FREE and open to all high school students.
Register today!
Link below!
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1wHigsmnZr30PM0Unfl6iNtVL3Xo5lF9h4mTGL2exb-Q/viewform?ts=5ecf15a6&edit_requested=true )

Over 1,000 Cars Anticipated to Participate in Compton Unified School District Drive Up Graduation Ceremony Parade and Stage Walk Today -- WATCH LIVE ON OUR WEBSITE STARTING AT 8AM

Despite the pandemic, we are determined to celebrate our graduatesâ€”we will do so all day today with over ONE THOUSAND cars anticipated to participate in three drive-up graduation parades and ceremonial stage walks high school seniors at Compton, Centennial and Dominguez High Schools. Students/families will parade in cars along a guided pathway leading to the main stage. Students will exit their car once it is near the main stage and collect a diploma cover, have their name called over the PA system and walk across the stage.

Those at home will be able to view the stream live at https://www.compton.k12.ca.us/district/classof2020/celebrate-on-social/cusd-graduation-2020. The live stream will begin at 8am. SEE WEBSITE FOR SCHEDULES OF TODAY'S CEREMONIES

post_text:
Due to Coronavirus (COVID-19), children who are eligible for free or reduced-price meals at school will get extra food benefits. These food benefits are called Pandemic EBT or P-EBT benefits. P-EBT benefits help families in California buy food when schools are closed because of the coronavirus emergency.

Families will get up to $365 per eligible child on their P-EBT card to use on food and groceries.

Families with children who get CalFresh, Medi-Cal or Foster Care benefits do not need to apply. Most will get their P-EBT card in the mail during the month of May. P-EBT cards will begin arriving around May 12, 2020.

Families with children who are eligible for free or reduced-price meals and who do not get their P-EBT card in the mail by about May 22, 2020 must apply online before June 30, 2020. The online application will be available beginning May 22, 2020 at ca.p-ebt.org.

Micah Ali Satra Zurita LoWanda Jones-Green Sandra Faye Harvey-Moss Charles Davis

St. John's Well Child and Family Center and Compton Unified School District Partner to Launch COVID-19 Mobile Testing Unit Site

Compton--As stark racial disparities around COVID-19 continue coming to light while deaths by the virus grow across the country, St. John's Well Child and Family Center -- a network of community health centers serving the largest population of African Americans in Los Angeles County and the largest population of undocumented people in the United States, and will be partnering with Compton Unified School District to serve one of those communities: Compton.
Micah Ali Satra Zurita Charles Davis LoWanda Jones-Green Sandra Faye Harvey-Moss

Be sure to complete the #2020Census today at https://2020census.gov.

Over the next ten years, lawmakers, business owners, and many others will use data to make critical decisions. The results will show where communities need new schools, new clinics, new roads, and more services for families, older adults, and children.

The results will also inform how hundreds of billions of dollars in federal funding are allocated to more than 100 programs, including Medicaid, Head Start, block grants for community mental health services, services for seniors and the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program, also known as SNAP.

post_text:
Statement from President Micah Ali and Superintendent Dr. Darin Brawley
April 8, 2020

In light of recent guidance from local and state agencies related to the unique health risks posed by the COVID-19 pandemic, the Compton Unified School District Board of Trustees at the April 8, 2020 Board of Trustees Meeting made a decision to extend school site closure for the remainder end of the school year, unless further and different guidance is received from State and local officials.

Although school sites and facilities are closed, learning will continue. We are grateful and proud of the tremendous work done to ensure that students have access to instruction. We are pleased to report that we are entering into Spring Break having ensured that almost 90% of our students have access to learning technology and over 90% of our teachers have established virtual classrooms for students.
text:
Statement from President Micah Ali and Superintendent Dr. Darin Brawley
April 8, 2020

In light of recent guidance from local and state agencies related to the unique health risks posed by the COVID-19 pandemic, the Compton Unified School District Board of Trustees at the April 8, 2020 Board of Trustees Meeting made a decision to extend school site closure for the remainder end of the school year, unless further and different guidance is received from State and local officials.

Although school sites and facilities are closed, learning will continue. We are grateful and proud of the tremendous work done to ensure that students have access to instruction. We are pleased to report that we are entering into Spring Break having ensured that almost 90% of our students have access to learning technology and over 90% of our teachers have established virtual classrooms for students.

January 3 at 4:05 PM Â·

Dear Jefferson Family

We hope each one of you had a rejuvenated and safe winter vacation. Let's start of 2020 filled with academic goals that will ensure our students to be successful towards their college and career readiness pathways such as attending school each day and on time, being prepared, and doing their very best each day. School will resume back this Monday, January 6, 2020 and we are very excited to welcome back our students, parents, teachers, staff, and the community. Let's make the year 2020 a successful year for the Jefferson community. Go Jaguars

Attention CUSD Parents/Guardians: Have you completed a Household Income Form for your child? They are due December 17th. This form helps provide funding for the great programs that our students enjoy across the district. Please speak to your school principal if you have not received a form. Each form already has the student's name on it, so all parents/guardians need to do is:

1. Fill in the Household Size bubble
2. Fill in the monthly income range bubble
3. Sign the form
4. Turn it into the school office

Micah Ali Satra Zurita Charles Davis LoWanda Jones-Green Alma Pleasant Sandra Faye Harvey-Moss
